A car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance company.
This agreement shall be signed in writing by means of an insurance contract which shall determine that the company will receive the agreed insurance premium and in return shall be obliged to submit the corresponding amount of the compensation in the event of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that is composed of several factors, including age, gender, time of drawing up the licence, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance undertakings set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are also due in the event of a higher risk of accident.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make less contributions, as statistics show that, due to their caution, these groups have a lower accident rate.
The same applies to married persons, as according to the statistical values and therefore also to the firm's conviction, they tend to suffer less accidents as a single person.
The benefit to the vehicle is affected by the frequency of the driving and therefore the probability of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In drawing up the premium, insurance must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that is most likely to meet his personal needs.
We now list the most important points that should be considered in the selection of insurance in order not only to make a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
The less than 25-year-olds encounter many obstacles in the choice of low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and young drivers' licences.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to be covered by full-cash insurance, there are still more expensive alternatives.
The cautious drivers can select a full-time cashier with self-participation, so that the services of a full-time insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract means that the customer must pay part of the amount resulting from the damage itself.
The amount will be fixed before the contract is concluded and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher than the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, the main representative of Spain at First Europe, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insurance the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused by his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's a piece of advice.
When you are under 25 years old, it is in your hand to reduce the insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the rates mentioned.
